  "prompt": "What's the temperature in an airliner's cargo hold?",
  "response": "The temperature in an airliner's cargo hold can vary depending on the aircraft and the specific hold within the aircraft. Generally, there are two types of cargo holds: pressurized and unpressurized.\n\n- **Pressurized Cargo Hold**: Most modern commercial airliners have pressurized cargo holds that are usually kept at similar temperatures to the passenger cabin. This is typically between 18\u00b0C to 24\u00b0C (64\u00b0F to 75\u00b0F). This ensures that both baggage and, if applicable, live animals are transported comfortably and safely.\n\n- **Unpressurized Cargo Hold**: Some older or smaller aircraft may have unpressurized cargo holds where temperatures can drop significantly at higher altitudes. Temperatures in these holds can be well below freezing during flight.\n\nHowever, it's important to check with the specific airline and aircraft model for precise information, as policies and configurations can vary.",
